      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "@Tim Edwards Did a bit more testing and they seem to perform just fine at 3.3V    Got rise time of 2 ns and fall time of 1 ns ( not sure of the load, it's a test pcb + scope probe so probably in the 20~30 pF range ). And the output still looked pretty square outputting a 75 MHz clock.   TBH they work better than the sky130 and IHP ones \uD83D\uDE05",
